The paper deals with approximation algorithms for submodular optimization problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the context of lower bounds for the approximability of these problems. Finally, the paper discusses graph cut problems, which are often studied in the area of computational complexity (cs.CC).
